==English==
===Intransitive verb===
'''[[pinch]] [[hit]]''', (past '''pinch hit''')

# {{idiom}} To do something in the place of another person who is not able to perform or is less skilled; to [[substitute]] or [[stand in]] for somebody.
#: ''Jones '''pinch hit''' for Smith during today's presentation.''
#{{baseball}} To [[bat]] in place of another player
#: ''Jones '''pinch hit''' for Smith in the sixth.''